e other day we were in velks. We were easily squashing what mobs we could get. (wish the crowds would go away) Well being as that we all constantly had an abundance of mana, the chanter and shaman buffed the casters and priests and we all figured &quot;might as well work on skill&quot;. OMG what a blast. Nothing funnier than watching a chanter wack away for her little 10pts a hit. But to our surprise, we were dropping mobs like stones. It became a massace. And as the crowd thinned out we were pulling more and more mobs yet we still were consistently abundant in mana and taking down mobs like bixies. Could this be the new combat philosophy? I tell ya this, it was alot more fun than sitting on my arse. Granted at times a member had to sit out a mob and med, but I've we never had so much fun before. And yes the enc had to break away to mez mobs but she did and we promptly massacred the adds. Now before you say &quot;yea well just try that with Velk&quot; How about we do? Could this be the way the game was intended? Why give cleric 9/24 1hb that proc dd's if they never get to use them? Do we only have them cause they give plus five wis? And, yes  i wasnt hiting for 150 a pop like the war standing next to me, but my little 30pt smacks added up. It reminded me of my old D&amp;D days where everyone joined in to the fray. But, no matter, I intend to continue this fighting style, even if only with firends who are open to the idea. (tried it later with strangers and at first it was working as before, but as old habits die hard and with our first hairy fight (in which we triumphed, the chanter at 60 upon its conclusion) the old sit on ur ass style was back.  /yawn.<br>
